I've wanted to fly since I was little.
And I did it today… today, I flew a plane. I'm still having a hard time believing it.
FlightAware data.
I'm going to try to go again on Saturday. The weather isn't great right now, but it's only Monday.
Difficulties are already starting to appear. I'm probably going to have A LOT of trouble getting a medical certificate, due to the FAA's position on certain medications.
Not impossible, but it's going to take ENORMOUSLY long and require A LOT of extra work.
Even though it's discouraging, it's just another problem to solve, and for now, it seems *completely* surmountable. It's just that it's going to take a lot of time and $$.
In case the challenge that awaits me interests you.
The FAA isn't a fan of ADHD. They don't issue a medical certificate if you're on treatment for it.
